00:07:27.196 --> 00:07:28.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really, Frankie?

137
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:32.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I've made myself perfectly clear.

138
00:07:32.910 --> 00:07:35.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not coming in
until you get rid of your--

139
00:07:35.413 --> 00:07:37.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're gonna have to come into the house
if you wanna keep berating me.

140
00:07:39.333 --> 00:07:40.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

141
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:46.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good. Now...

142
00:07:48.217 --> 00:07:51.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we're gonna have to send out an email
blast to drive people to our website.

143
00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:53.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We need traffic.
-Whoa. Slow your roll.

144
00:07:54.015 --> 00:07:56.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
None of that's happening
until you get rid of that gun.

145
00:07:56.392 --> 00:07:57.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I get it. You're mad.

146
00:07:58.060 --> 00:07:59.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We were both upset last night.

147
00:08:00.021 --> 00:08:02.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A gun was fired. A doll was shot.

148
00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:07.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A "doll"? A decoy, of me,
with some of my actual hair!

149
00:08:07.695 --> 00:08:09.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But it wasn't you.

150
00:08:09.822 --> 00:08:12.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it were, then, yes, it would be bad.

151
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:14.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Prison bad.

152
00:08:14.535 --> 00:08:18.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You held my face in your hands
and promised me.

153
00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:22.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie, I have had that gun for 15 years.

154
00:08:22.251 --> 00:08:25.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have had it at the beach house
this whole time.

155
00:08:25.087 --> 00:08:27.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You didn't care
when you didn't know about it.

156
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:30.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why can't you just go back
and not know about it?

157
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:34.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know we've had our shit, but at least
we've always been honest with each other.

158
00:08:37.099 --> 00:08:39.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, okay?

159
00:08:41.562 --> 00:08:43.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can we please just move on?

160
00:08:43.356 --> 00:08:46.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sure. Fine. No problem.

161
00:08:46.651 --> 00:08:48.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Except no fucking way.

162
00:08:51.155 --> 00:08:52.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

163
00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:01.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

164
00:09:01.999 --> 00:09:05.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
May the truth live in my mind,
on my lips, and in my heart.

165
00:09:23.437 --> 00:09:24.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello, Mother.

166
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:26.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Robert.

167
00:09:29.860 --> 00:09:31.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I wasn't expecting you.

168
00:09:32.613 --> 00:09:33.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

169
00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:36.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did my birthday come twice this year,

170
00:09:37.034 --> 00:09:39.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or were you afraid I'd die
before Christmas?

171
00:09:39.161 --> 00:09:41.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're never gonna die.
You're far too stubborn.

172
00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:48.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your Aunt Ann came by last month.

173
00:09:48.629 --> 00:09:51.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-So you're speaking to each other again?
-No.

174
00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:53.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And how is Uncle Billy?

175
00:09:53.884 --> 00:09:55.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not speaking to him, either.

176
00:09:57.680 --> 00:09:59.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that you're working on?

177
00:10:00.891 --> 00:10:05.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Friday's crossword. Once I finish this,
I have nothing left to live for.

178
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:07.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I brought you something.

179
00:10:07.732 --> 00:10:09.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a Kindle.

180
00:10:09.108 --> 00:10:12.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's really amazing. You just tell me
all the books you want to read,

181
00:10:12.778 --> 00:10:17.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I order them online, and they show up
right in here almost immediately.

182
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:19.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all done electronically.

183
00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:22.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes. I know what a Kindle is, dear.

184
00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:23.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mrs. Montgomery has one.

185
00:10:23.831 --> 00:10:24.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, good.

186
00:10:24.999 --> 00:10:28.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She doesn't like it. It's too bright.
She says it hurts her eyes.

187
00:10:28.586 --> 00:10:31.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I can adjust the brightness for you.

188
00:10:31.088 --> 00:10:32.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know.

189
00:10:32.882 --> 00:10:36.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suppose it seems a little...
self-indulgent

190
00:10:36.802 --> 00:10:39.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
not even to be able
to turn your own pages.

191
00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:42.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd miss the feeling
of earning my pleasure.

192
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:44.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right. [chuckles]

193
00:10:47.772 --> 00:10:49.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So why did you come to see me today?

194
00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:56.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I, uh, just wanted to talk about...
stuff in my life.

195
00:10:56.614 --> 00:10:58.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't mumble.

196
00:10:59.325 --> 00:11:00.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is everyone okay? The girls?

197
00:11:00.993 --> 00:11:02.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, everyone's fine. It's nothing bad.

198
00:11:02.953 --> 00:11:05.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's what you said when you told me
about the divorce.

199
00:11:06.457 --> 00:11:10.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. Well, actually, I...

200
00:11:11.962 --> 00:11:14.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
want you to know that I, uh...

201
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:16.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
recently got remarried.

202
00:11:17.426 --> 00:11:18.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

203
00:11:19.428 --> 00:11:22.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess my invitation
got lost in the mail. Who is she?

204
00:11:22.848 --> 00:11:24.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How young is she?

205
00:11:27.686 --> 00:11:29.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You remember Sol?

206
00:11:29.897 --> 00:11:31.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean the loud Jew from the law firm?

207
00:11:32.441 --> 00:11:37.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You usually mention he's also tall,
but, yes, that's the one.

208
00:11:37.488 --> 00:11:38.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about him?

209
00:11:39.573 --> 00:11:41.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's the one I married.

210
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

211
00:11:45.413 --> 00:11:46.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I married Sol.

212
00:11:49.333 --> 00:11:50.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh-ho.

213
00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:52.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This is because of Grace, isn't it?
-What?

214
00:11:52.837 --> 00:11:56.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So you married the wrong woman,
but that doesn't mean that you're--

215
00:11:56.966 --> 00:11:57.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gay.

216
00:11:58.884 --> 00:12:00.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it does.

217
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am gay.

218
00:12:03.764 --> 00:12:07.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And a man named Sol Bergstein
is the love of my life.

219
00:12:08.310 --> 00:12:11.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And now I'm lucky enough
to call him my husband.

220
00:12:12.022 --> 00:12:15.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I probably should have started
with the "I'm gay" thing,

221
00:12:15.985 --> 00:12:17.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I thought if I...

222
00:12:19.196 --> 00:12:24.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
mentioned the "I married a man" thing
it would clue you right in.

223
00:12:30.499 --> 00:12:32.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you going to say anything?

224
00:12:32.710 --> 00:12:34.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want me to say?

225
00:12:34.879 --> 00:12:35.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

226
00:12:36.756 --> 00:12:37.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're happy for me?

227
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:41.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine. I'm happy for you.

228
00:12:47.224 --> 00:12:51.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What? You surely weren't expecting
some kind of blessing for this.

229
00:12:51.687 --> 00:12:52.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

230
00:12:53.397 --> 00:12:54.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I...

231
00:12:55.858 --> 00:12:58.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
was kind of hoping you'd surprise me.

232
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Surprise? I don't do that.

233
00:13:05.534 --> 00:13:09.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He is really a wonderful man.

234
00:13:10.581 --> 00:13:12.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's everything to me.

235
00:13:15.711 --> 00:13:18.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you know,
you are just like your father.

236
00:13:18.422 --> 00:13:19.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gay? [chuckles]

237
00:13:20.049 --> 00:13:21.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Selfish.

238
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:24.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were always a selfish boy.

239
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:26.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, I see you've grown
into a selfish man.

240
00:13:28.599 --> 00:13:29.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

241
00:13:29.517 --> 00:13:34.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could have happily died never knowing
that you were one of them.

242
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:38.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

243
00:13:39.318 --> 00:13:40.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Goodbye.

244
00:13:42.738 --> 00:13:43.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Robert?

245
00:13:45.741 --> 00:13:46.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes?

246
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:50.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you take that Kindle thing
with you. I'm never going to use it.

247
00:14:03.092 --> 00:14:04.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[voice mail beeps]

248
00:14:05.219 --> 00:14:06.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, love.

249
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:09.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just wanting to know how it went,
and hoping you're doing all right.

250
00:14:09.890 --> 00:14:11.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let me know--
-[phone rings]

251
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:14.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, hang on. The other line is ringing.

252
00:14:17.606 --> 00:14:20.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey, hang on one second.
I'm on the other line.

253
00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:23.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll call you back. Or you call me back.

254
00:14:25.573 --> 00:14:28.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sorry about that, Frankie.
-It's the other one.

255
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:30.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

256
00:14:31.328 --> 00:14:36.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hi, Grace. Robert's not here.
He drove up north to visit Cruella de Vil.

257
00:14:36.375 --> 00:14:38.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's your mother-in-law now. Enjoy.

258
00:14:39.003 --> 00:14:40.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

259
00:14:40.379 --> 00:14:42.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually, I'm calling for you.

260
00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:43.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, okay.

261
00:14:44.842 --> 00:14:47.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you seen Frankie by any chance?

262
00:14:47.177 --> 00:14:48.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. Is everything okay?

263
00:14:49.054 --> 00:14:50.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[stammers] Uh, yes. Fine.

264
00:14:50.639 --> 00:14:55.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just, um... she left at noon
and I haven't seen her all day.

265
00:14:55.477 --> 00:14:57.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When was the last time she checked in?

266
00:14:57.313 --> 00:15:00.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs] She, um... she hasn't checked in.

267
00:15:00.357 --> 00:15:05.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Huh. I mean, she once checked in
from the back of a minivan I was driving.

268
00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:07.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles] I know.

269
00:15:07.781 --> 00:15:10.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did something happen?
<i>-We had a fight.</i>

270
00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:14.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, nothing crazy, but just our usual
odd couple shenanigans.

271
00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:17.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She seemed especially heated, though.

272
00:15:17.833 --> 00:15:20.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Must have been. She didn't even call me
to complain about you.

273
00:15:20.794 --> 00:15:22.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Did you call the boys?</i>

274
00:15:22.546 --> 00:15:26.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, and they've already called
all the Del Tacos. Nothing.

275
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:28.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How about the "Find My iPhone" app?

276
00:15:29.053 --> 00:15:33.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did that. The man at the gas station who's
had it for a week wasn't very helpful.

277
00:15:33.974 --> 00:15:35.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe she's with Jacob?

278
00:15:35.893 --> 00:15:38.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
